  "response": "The POSIX-portable way to do this:\n\n```sh\nsed 's/foo/bar/g' file.txt > tmp && mv tmp file.txt\n```\n\nKey points:\n\n- The `g` flag on the `s` command replaces **all** occurrences per line, not just the first.\n- **Do not use `sed -i`** \u2014 the `-i` (in-place) flag is a GNU/BSD extension and not part of POSIX.\n- The portable pattern is: redirect to a temp file, then `mv` it back over the original.\n\nReplace `file.txt` with your actual filename.",
